==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Orientalist
<hw>O`ri*en"tal*ist</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>orientaliste</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>An inhabitant of the Eastern parts of the world; an
Oriental.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One versed in Eastern languages, literature, etc.;
<as>as, the Paris Congress of <ex>Orientalists</ex></as>.</def>
<rj><au>Sir J. Shore.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Orientality</ent>⟦br⟧
